8)  Trust yourself and don't expect anything from anyone.
There was a beautiful old cold town in the north of Europe that had a main door to enter and to exit, by the door there was a doorman shivering from the cold each night after the sunset. Every single night, the doorman used to light up the fire to survive until the morning because of the strong cold. 
One of the cold early nights, the king entered the town and saw the doorman sitting right next to the fire shivering. The king ordered his soldiers to stop the horse carriage to talk to the doorman.
'It seems you are very cold.' Said the king to the doorman.
'Yes my king the cold is so strong, I am lighting up and keeping the fire going till the morning so I don't freeze from cold.' Said the doorman.
The king; 'I will send you a warm coat that kills the cold with one of my soldiers when I reach my castle, so you don't shiver anymore'. Then the king left.
The doorman was so happy no more fighting cold anymore. The king went back to his castle and got busy with his family and the towns' affairs with his ministers. The king forgot to send the coat to the doorman. In the morning while the king was drinking his coffee, the soldiers came to him with the sad news of the doorman; 'My king, the doorman died from the cold. And we found this letter in his frozen hand with the title 'To the king.' The king took the letter and opened and read the following; 'My king, I was holding on myself and fighting the cold every night until the sun rose and went to see my family. But when I relied on you to bring me a coat with one of your soldiers I gave up to cold and here I am writing this letter for you before I die that you promise killed me and not the cold. You promised to get me a coat when you reached the castle and I kept waiting for your soldier to come with the coat and that never happened. I wish I didn't expect anything from you. Take care of my family.'
Moral of the story: 
Don't you ever rely on anyone, don't you ever expect any help from others, and don't you ever expect anything from anyone. Be strong yourself, relying and expecting from others will definitely destroy you emotionally, make you sad, you toss and turn a lot in your bed losing sleep by the toxic overthinking. 
